  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read both deploy notes (task 063 + task 064) to capture dev environment URLs and confirm both deploys succeeded.</step>
    <step order="2">**Context A — Standalone SummarizeFilesWizard solution**: navigate to the surface where the wizard launches in dev (per the solution's expected entry point — likely from a related record or a launcher button).</step>
    <step order="3">Run the wizard: select 2-3 files → progress through summarization steps → reach the email step.</step>
    <step order="4">Verify visual: inline mount renders without internal header/action bar (per NFR-03); the wizard chrome owns navigation. Auto-generated summary appears as `initialBody`.</step>
    <step order="5">Fill the email step: To = test recipient, Subject = "Wave 4 smoke test standalone". Click the wizard's Finish/Send button.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify success: toast appears, dialog/wizard closes. In Dataverse, query `sprk_communication` for the new record. Verify: `statuscode = Sent`, `sprk_internetmessageid` populated, body contains the summary, file attachments linked. Record `sprk_communicationid` GUID.</step>
    <step order="7">**Context B — LegalWorkspace**: navigate to the surface that previously mounted the fork (varies; check `current-task.md` audit list from task 061 for consumer location).</step>
    <step order="8">Repeat steps 3-6 in the LegalWorkspace context. Subject = "Wave 4 smoke test legalworkspace". Record `sprk_communicationid` GUID.</step>
    <step order="9">**Validation tests (one context only — Context A or B)**: run TO_REQUIRED + TO_INVALID_EMAIL cases. Verify canonical wrapper surfaces correct error codes.</step>
    <step order="10">**Network observation (both contexts)**: open DevTools Network. Confirm exactly ONE POST to `/api/communications/send` per send action. Zero non-canonical request paths.</step>
    <step order="11">Compile results into `notes/test-results/065-summarize-smoke.md` with structure:
      <code>
      # Wave 4 SummarizeFilesWizard Smoke Test
      Date: [date]
      Tester: [name]

      ## Context A — Standalone SummarizeFilesWizard solution
      Environment: [dev URL from wave-4-deploy-summarize.md]
      - Wizard navigation pass: ✅ / ❌
      - Email step renders inline (no internal chrome): ✅ / ❌
      - Send: ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL
      - sprk_communicationid: [GUID]
      - sprk_internetmessageid populated: yes / no
      - Attachments linked: yes / no
      - Network: single POST to /api/communications/send: ✅ / ❌

      ## Context B — LegalWorkspace
      Environment: [dev URL from wave-4-deploy-legalworkspace.md]
      - Wizard navigation pass: ✅ / ❌
      - Email step renders inline: ✅ / ❌
      - Send: ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL
      - sprk_communicationid: [GUID]
      - sprk_internetmessageid populated: yes / no
      - Attachments linked: yes / no
      - Network: single POST: ✅ / ❌

      ## Validation tests (Context A or B)
      - TO_REQUIRED: ✅ / ❌
      - TO_INVALID_EMAIL: ✅ / ❌

      ## Issues / Defects
      [List any defects]
      </code>
    </step>
    <step order="12">If smoke fails in EITHER context: escalate. Standalone fail → task 060 (shared canonical defect). LegalWorkspace fail → task 062 (consumer retarget defect). Do NOT mark complete until both pass.</step>
    <step order="13">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 065 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="14">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed, advance to next pending task (070 — Wave 5 start).</step>
  </steps>

